			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">The NaCl plugin's __sendAsyncMessage*() methods (from issue 642) do not support strings containing nulls.  The message to send will be truncated at the first null byte, because it is treated as a C string internally.

This means anyone using this interface to send binary data (e.g. for the initial argv/env message) will have to work around this limitation and use an indirect encoding.

Note, however, that this is only an experimental interface.
